        <fact xml:id="fact-SQ6comparesequence">
            <statement>
            <p>
                Supppose we have sequences <m>\{a_n\}, \{b_n\}</m> so that for some <m>k</m> we have that <m>0\leq b_n\leq a_n</m> for each <m>k\geq n</m>. Then we have the following results:
                <ul>
                    <li>If <m>\displaystyle\sum_{k=n}^\infty a_n</m> converges, then so does  <m>\displaystyle\sum_{k=n}^\infty b_n</m>.</li>
                    <li>If <m>\displaystyle\sum_{k=n}^\infty b_n</m> diverges, then so does  <m>\displaystyle\sum_{k=n}^\infty a_n</m>.</li>
                </ul>
            </p>
           </statement>     
        </fact>
        
        
